  - If `m` is an upper bound for `S`, set `[aₙ₊₁, bₙ₊₁] = [aₙ, m]`
  - If not, find some `s ∈ S` with `s > m`, set `[aₙ₊₁, bₙ₊₁] = [s, bₙ]`

